	{
		"id": "pair_mira_yselle_right_memory",
		"unit_a": "Mira Ashdown",
		"unit_b": "Yselle Maris",
		"title": "Right Memory",
		"text": "Yselle hums under her breath as she mends a torn costume ribbon. Mira, nearby, is restringing her bow with careful hands.\n\n\"That song,\" Mira says. \"It makes ruins sound prettier than they were.\"\nYselle stills. \"That was not my intention.\"\n\"I know.\" Mira’s voice softens. \"I just… don’t want people loving what happened to us more than they loved us before it did.\"\nYselle sets the ribbon down. \"Then tell me something true. Not dramatic. Just true.\"\nMira thinks for a moment. \"The south roof leaked every spring. The baker sang badly. The square smelled like apples after rain.\"\nYselle smiles, small and serious. \"Good,\" she says. \"That is where the song should start.\"",
