	{
		"id": "pair_branik_alden_bread_and_weight",
		"unit_a": "Branik",
		"unit_b": "Brother Alden",
		"title": "Bread and Weight",
		"text": "Branik is kneading dough with his usual terrifying competence when Alden steps into the cookfire glow.\n\n\"You work like a man trying to apologize to flour,\" Alden says.\nBranik huffs a laugh. \"Flour’s easier than people. It tells you when you’ve pushed too hard.\"\nAlden leans on the table. \"People do too. Just less honestly.\"\nBranik goes quiet for a moment, then says, \"I spent a long time being useful because I did not know how to be forgiven.\"\nAlden nods as if that is not a shocking confession at all. \"Then it is fortunate this camp keeps needing both bread and practice.\"\nBranik’s smile is tired, but real. \"That may be the kindest sermon I’ve ever heard.\"",
