	{
		"id": "pair_maela_pell_height_and_heart",
		"unit_a": "Maela Thorn",
		"unit_b": "Pell Rowan",
		"title": "Height and Heart",
		"text": "Pell nearly drops his practice spear when Maela lands beside him from the wagon roof.\n\n\"Do you always arrive like divine punishment?\" he blurts.\nMaela grins. \"Only for people with especially funny expressions.\"\nHe tries to recover his dignity and fails nobly. \"I was rehearsing.\" \n\"I know,\" she says, gentler now. \"You rehearse courage like it’s a speech.\"\nPell looks down. \"Is that bad?\"\nMaela hooks a thumb toward the dark sky. \"No. It just means you think bravery happens before the fall. Usually it happens during.\" She nudges his shoulder with hers. \"Good news, though. You’re still trying on the way down. That counts for more than style.\"",
