	{
		"id": "pair_hadrien_liora_light_without_fear",
		"unit_a": "Ser Hadrien",
		"unit_b": "Liora",
		"title": "Light Without Fear",
		"text": "Liora has finished a quiet prayer when Hadrien’s spectral glow gathers at the edge of the shrine.\n\n\"Your age and mine used some of the same words,\" he says.\nLiora lowers her hands. \"I know. That is part of the trouble.\"\nThe old knight inclines his head. \"And yet you still speak them.\"\n\"Because I am trying to keep the mercy and bury the machinery built around it,\" she replies.\nHadrien is silent for a long moment. \"Then perhaps you are doing what none of us managed in time.\"\nLiora’s eyes shine, but she does not look away. \"I would settle for doing it before more people die of our certainty.\" \n\"A worthy revision,\" Hadrien says softly.",
