	{
		"id": "pair_tamsin_liora_hands_that_stay",
		"unit_a": "Tamsin Reed",
		"unit_b": "Liora",
		"title": "Hands That Stay",
		"text": "Tamsin is trying and failing to hide the shake in her hands while sorting dried herbs. Liora quietly takes the bowl before it spills.\n\n\"I’m fine,\" Tamsin says too quickly.\n\"You are useful,\" Liora replies. \"That is not the same thing.\"\nTamsin blinks at her.\nLiora sets the bowl down and begins dividing the herbs into neater piles. \"You are allowed to become tired before you become useless. The order we were given on that point was… not merciful.\"\nTamsin lets out a weak, startled laugh. \"That might be the most frighteningly kind thing anyone’s said to me all week.\"\nLiora’s mouth twitches. \"Then sit. Frightening kindness can continue while seated.\"",
