	{
		"id": "pair_garrick_sabine_perimeter_of_honor",
		"unit_a": "Garrick Vale",
		"unit_b": "Sabine Varr",
		"title": "Perimeter of Honor",
		"text": "Sabine is checking the night perimeter when Garrick falls into step beside her.\n\n\"You do your own inspections,\" he notes.\n\"I distrust delegated certainty,\" she replies.\nHe gives a low hum of approval. \"Sensibly put. Edranor had too much confidence in uniforms and too little in outcomes.\"\nSabine glances at him. \"You still talk about honor as if it might recover.\"\nGarrick’s answer comes after a pause. \"Not recover. Earn. Again. There is a difference.\"\nFor the rest of the round, they walk in companionable silence, two professionals keeping faith with the parts of duty that still deserve it.",
