	{
		"id": "pair_rufus_branik_feeding_the_living",
		"unit_a": "Rufus",
		"unit_b": "Branik",
		"title": "Feeding the Living",
		"text": "Rufus shoulders a sack of grain into the cook area and drops it with a grunt. Branik catches it before it topples.\n\n\"You carry supplies like they insulted your family,\" Branik says.\n\"Most supplies have,\" Rufus replies. \"Usually by not existing when needed.\"\nBranik ties the sack open and checks the grain with careful fingers. \"Still. We’ve got enough tonight.\"\nRufus watches him for a moment. \"That matters more than speeches ever do. A hot meal tells people tomorrow exists.\"\nBranik’s expression softens. \"Then let’s be rude enough to keep proving it.\"",
