	{
		"id": "pair_inez_mira_names_for_ruins",
		"unit_a": "Inez",
		"unit_b": "Mira Ashdown",
		"title": "Names for Ruins",
		"text": "Mira is scraping mud from her boots when Inez approaches with a small bundle of herbs.\n\n\"For smoke-sickness,\" Inez says, offering them.\nMira takes them carefully. \"Thank you.\"\nThey stand in silence for a while, watching the tree line.\n\"People keep trying to name what happened to Oakhaven for me,\" Mira says at last.\nInez’s mouth tightens. \"Outsiders love names. Makes theft feel organized.\"\nMira laughs once, sharp and surprised. \"Yes.\"\nInez nods toward the herbs. \"Then keep your own names for it. The true ones. Land remembers better when the living do too.\"",
