	{
		"id": "pair_tariq_corvin_wrong_questions",
		"unit_a": "Tariq",
		"unit_b": "Corvin Ash",
		"title": "Wrong Questions",
		"text": "Tariq finds Corvin near the ward-stakes, staring at nothing visible in a way that feels professionally offensive.\n\n\"You have the posture of a man about to make scholarship everyone else’s problem,\" Tariq says.\nCorvin glances at him. \"Only because everyone else insists on making ignorance communal.\"\nTariq actually smiles at that. \"There you are. I was worried you’d become respectable.\"\nCorvin’s expression shifts by a fraction. \"And I was worried you’d confuse cynicism with caution forever.\"\nTariq folds his arms. \"I do not confuse them. I layer them.\" \n\"Ah,\" Corvin says. \"Then perhaps there is hope for you yet.\"",
