	{
		"id": "pair_maela_yselle_grace_in_motion",
		"unit_a": "Maela Thorn",
		"unit_b": "Yselle Maris",
		"title": "Grace in Motion",
		"text": "Yselle watches Maela balance along the top of a supply cart as if the wagon were a stage built for one.\n\n\"That is either an entrance or a cry for attention,\" Yselle says.\nMaela beams. \"Why choose?\"\nYselle laughs, then studies her more carefully. \"You move like someone who trusts falling.\"\nMaela hops down, lighter now. \"No. I move like someone who got tired of asking the ground for permission.\"\nYselle’s smile softens into something warmer. \"That,\" she says, \"is a line worth stealing.\"\n\"Take it,\" Maela replies. \"I’ve got more.\"",
