		{
		"id": "pair_darian_yselle_velvet_knives",
		"unit_a": "Darian",
		"unit_b": "Yselle Maris",
		"title": "Velvet Knives",
		"text": "Yselle is unpinning stage ribbons from her sleeves when Darian appears with two cups and the sort of smile that usually means trouble.\n\n\"You handed a room its own reflection tonight,\" he says.\nYselle accepts the cup carefully. \"And you looked offended they recognized themselves.\"\nHe laughs under his breath. \"Only impressed. Most people can’t wound with grace.\"\n\"That sounds perilously like flirting,\" she says.\nDarian’s gaze lingers a fraction too long. \"No,\" he replies softly. \"Flirting is kinder. That was professional admiration.\"\nYselle looks down into the steam so he cannot quite see her smile. \"Dangerous distinction,\" she murmurs.",
