	{
		"id": "pair_maela_mira_roofline_breath",
		"unit_a": "Maela Thorn",
		"unit_b": "Mira Ashdown",
		"title": "Roofline Breath",
		"text": "Mira climbs onto the wagon roof expecting solitude and finds Maela already there, knees drawn up, watching the stars like they owe her gossip.\n\n\"You too?\" Maela asks.\n\"It’s quieter up here,\" Mira says.\n\"That’s because fear has to work harder when it wants to follow you onto a roof.\"\nMira snorts despite herself. For a while they sit in companionable silence.\nThen Maela says, very gently, \"You don’t always have to remember from the ground.\"\nMira’s throat tightens. \"No?\"\n\"No.\" Maela tips her face toward the sky. \"Sometimes it helps to remember from somewhere the fire never reached.\"",
