	{
		"id": "pair_hest_tamsin_smoke_and_salves",
		"unit_a": "Hest \"Sparks\"",
		"unit_b": "Tamsin Reed",
		"title": "Smoke and Salves",
		"text": "Tamsin is cataloguing salves when Hest bursts into the tent smelling faintly of smoke and triumph.\n\n\"Good news,\" Hest says. \"Nothing exploded in a medically significant way.\"\nTamsin closes her eyes. \"That sentence contains too much uncertainty.\"\nHest sets down a bent metal bracket. \"I came for balm. And maybe reassurance. In that order.\"\nTamsin reaches for the salve with a sigh that is mostly fondness now. \"Sit. If you drip molten nonsense on my floor again, I’ll start charging you by the panic.\"\nHest beams. \"That is the nicest threat anyone’s made all day.\"",
