	{
		"id": "pair_pell_tamsin_keep_breathing",
		"unit_a": "Pell Rowan",
		"unit_b": "Tamsin Reed",
		"title": "Keep Breathing",
		"text": "Pell is reciting a training mantra under his breath when Tamsin passes with a tray of poultices.\n\n\"You sound like you’re trying to negotiate with your lungs,\" she says.\nHe flushes. \"It helps. Before drills. Before battle. Before… everything, really.\"\nTamsin shifts the tray to one arm. \"Then maybe stop asking your breathing to win the war for you. Let it just be breathing.\"\nHe stares at her. \"Can it do that?\"\nFor the first time all day, Tamsin smiles without apology. \"Yes. That’s the wonderful part. Some things are allowed to help without being heroic.\"",
