	{
		"id": "pair_kaelen_meris_names_for_guilt",
		"unit_a": "Kaelen",
		"unit_b": "Sister Meris",
		"title": "Names for Guilt",
		"text": "Meris is burning old scrap orders one strip at a time when Kaelen pauses beside the brazier.\n\n\"Ceremonial?\" he asks.\n\"Cowardly,\" she answers. \"I do not know the proper distinction anymore.\"\nHe watches the ash fold in on itself. \"There are many names for guilt. Duty. Penance. Tradition. Necessity.\"\nMeris lets out a brittle laugh. \"You say that like a man who has tried them all.\"\nKaelen’s expression doesn’t change, which is answer enough. After a moment he adds, \"The trick is finding one that doesn’t ask someone else to carry it for you.\"\nMeris feeds another strip to the fire. \"I suspected you would say something unbearable and useful.\"",
