	{
		"id": "pair_corvin_hadrien_dust_of_saints",
		"unit_a": "Corvin Ash",
		"unit_b": "Ser Hadrien",
		"title": "Dust of Saints",
		"text": "Corvin stands within the old chapel ruins, studying stone that remembers too much. Hadrien’s ghost-light gathers beside a weathered arch.\n\n\"You built monuments to certainty,\" Corvin says, not looking at him.\n\"We built shelters for fear,\" Hadrien replies. \"Then mistook the shelter for the truth.\"\nCorvin turns at that, surprised into honesty. \"That may be the most intelligent thing any dead knight has ever said to me.\"\nHadrien’s mouth curves faintly. \"A low bar, I suspect.\"\nCorvin looks back at the broken altar. \"Do you ever wish the Order had simply vanished cleanly?\"\n\"No,\" Hadrien says. \"Clean endings teach the living nothing. Ruins are harder. Better.\"",
