	{
		"id": "pair_sabine_meris_cold_mercy",
		"unit_a": "Sabine Varr",
		"unit_b": "Sister Meris",
		"title": "Cold Mercy",
		"text": "Sabine is reviewing prisoner supply requests when Meris stops at her table.\n\n\"You approved the blankets,\" Meris says.\n\"Of course I did,\" Sabine replies. \"Cold does not improve truth. It only cheapens the people using it.\"\nMeris studies her for a long moment. \"You say mercy like a logistical principle.\"\nSabine finally looks up. \"And you say it like a relic.\"\nFor a breath, the air between them is sharp.\nThen Meris nods once. \"Perhaps it has been both for too long.\"\nSabine slides the ledger toward her. \"Then let us try administration instead of sanctimony and see if the world notices.\"",
