	{
		"id": "pair_rufus_veska_after_impact",
		"unit_a": "Rufus",
		"unit_b": "Veska Moor",
		"title": "After Impact",
		"text": "Rufus is hammering a bent plate back into shape when Veska sets her shield beside the anvil.\n\n\"Yours too?\" he asks.\n\"Mine always,\" she says.\nHe runs a thumb over a deep dent. \"Funny thing. People think holding the line looks noble. From back here it mostly looks expensive.\"\nVeska’s laugh is low and tired. \"And repetitive.\"\nHe nods. \"Still did it.\"\nShe rests a hand on the shield’s rim. \"Still will.\"\nRufus gives the metal one last strike and hands it back. \"Good. I’d hate to repair something that didn’t intend to survive me doing it.\"",
