	},
	{
		"id": "pair_yselle_pell_courage_without_audience",
		"unit_a": "Yselle Maris",
		"unit_b": "Pell Rowan",
		"title": "Courage Without an Audience",
		"text": "Pell is practicing introductions under his breath when Yselle catches the end of one and nearly laughs.\n\n\"Please tell me that was meant for a duke,\" she says.\nPell goes scarlet. \"I was trying to sound… composed.\"\nYselle softens immediately. \"Forgive me. It was earnest, not foolish. Those are different things.\"\nHe rubs the back of his neck. \"I keep wanting bravery to sound better than it feels.\"\nYselle steps closer, voice warm now. \"Most real courage happens offstage, Pell. No applause. No lighting. Just a person deciding not to turn away.\" \nHe nods slowly. \"That sounds harder.\"\n\"It is,\" she says. \"That’s why it matters.\"",
