	{
		"id": "pair_nyx_maela_not_falling",
		"unit_a": "Nyx",
		"unit_b": "Maela Thorn",
		"title": "Not Falling",
		"text": "Maela is balanced on the camp palisade like gravity is a rumor when Nyx appears below, unimpressed.\n\n\"One day,\" Nyx says, \"you are going to do that in front of someone who mistakes panic for care.\"\nMaela grins down at them. \"You say that like you’d be worried.\"\nNyx crosses their arms. \"I say that like I dislike paperwork caused by preventable idiocy.\"\nMaela hops down lightly, still smiling. \"That’s practically affection in your dialect.\"\nNyx’s expression betrays them for half a second. \"Don’t get greedy,\" they mutter.\nMaela laughs, bright and warm. \"Too late.\"",
