	{
		"id": "pair_liora_meris_revised_prayer",
		"unit_a": "Liora",
		"unit_b": "Sister Meris",
		"title": "Revised Prayer",
		"text": "Liora is copying a litany into a fresh notebook when Meris pauses behind her.\n\n\"You changed the wording,\" Meris says.\n\"Yes,\" Liora replies. \"The old line asked for obedience before mercy. I thought I’d try the reverse.\"\nMeris stares at the page as if it has insulted a century of architecture. \"You can do that?\"\nLiora looks up, almost smiling. \"We changed far crueler things and still called them doctrine. I refuse to believe kindness is the one part too sacred to edit.\"\nSomething in Meris’s face tightens, then softens. \"May I see?\"\nLiora turns the notebook toward her without hesitation. \"Please.\"",
