	},
		{
		"id": "pair_kaelen_nyx_after_dawnkeep_truth",
		"unit_a": "Kaelen",
		"unit_b": "Nyx",
		"title": "After the Truth",
		"text": "Nyx finds Kaelen sitting awake long after the fires have burned low, one hand braced against the wagon wheel as if the earth might tilt without warning.\n\n\"You look awful,\" Nyx says.\n\"Your bedside manner remains inspiring,\" Kaelen replies.\nThey crouch across from him, all sarcasm stripped down to something leaner. \"You don’t have to earn the right to collapse after this.\"\nHe lets out a breath that sounds older than the night. \"It is difficult to tell the difference between resting and letting everyone down.\"\nNyx’s jaw tightens. \"Then borrow mine. I’m excellent at deciding who gets to fall apart and who gets left alone about it.\"\nKaelen looks at them, really looks, and the ghost of a smile finally reaches his face. \"That is an alarming offer.\"\n\"Yes,\" Nyx says softly. \"Take it anyway.\"",
