	{
		"id": "pair_kaelen_liora_after_order_ruins",
		"unit_a": "Kaelen",
		"unit_b": "Liora",
		"title": "What We Keep",
		"text": "Liora is folding a torn altar cloth into something smaller and more useful when Kaelen stops beside her.\n\n\"You’re repurposing relics,\" he says.\n\"I’m refusing to let them keep pretending they were innocent,\" Liora answers.\nHe is quiet for a long moment. \"I used to think preserving the Order meant preserving its shape.\"\nShe smooths the cloth once with both palms. \"And now?\"\nKaelen looks toward the ruined chapel. \"Now I think if anything holy survived us, it was never the stone.\" \nLiora’s eyes shine with exhausted relief. \"Good,\" she says. \"Because I do not know how to save walls anymore. Only people.\"\nHis voice softens. \"That was always the better liturgy.\"",
