		"unit_a": "Corvin Ash",
		"unit_b": "Sister Meris",
		"title": "No Clean Hands",
		"text": "Corvin finds Meris washing her hands in a basin that has long since gone cold.\n\n\"You’ll take the skin off at that rate,\" he observes.\n\"It would hardly be the first useful thing pain accomplished,\" she replies.\nHe leans against the tent post, expression unreadable. \"A disappointing theory. Pain is efficient, yes. Useful? Rarely.\"\nMeris does not look up. \"You speak like a man untroubled by consequence.\"\n\"No,\" Corvin says, softer than she expected. \"I speak like a man who has learned that guilt is not purification. It is only weight.\"\nThat finally makes her still.\n\"Then what is left?\" she asks.\nCorvin watches the water tremble around her hands. \"Choice,\" he says. \"Repeated until it begins to resemble a soul again.\"",
