	{
		"id": "pair_sabine_rufus_the_people_after",
		"unit_a": "Sabine Varr",
		"unit_b": "Rufus",
		"title": "The People After",
		"text": "Rufus is repairing a ration cart wheel when Sabine arrives with a ledger tucked under one arm.\n\n\"We can provision for the siege,\" she says. \"The harder question is after.\"\nHe keeps working. \"After is when policy gets shy about bodies.\"\nSabine exhales, almost a laugh. \"That may be the most concise strategic doctrine I have heard in years.\"\nHe glances up at her. \"I’m serious. Everyone plans for the battle. No one likes planning for the people who remain standing in the mud afterward asking what victory is supposed to taste like.\"\nShe looks down at the ledger in her hands, then closes it. \"Then let us be unpopular and plan for them anyway.\"\nRufus nods once. \"Good. That’s usually where the decent work starts.\"",
