	{
		"id": "pair_mira_branik_when_home_is_smell",
		"unit_a": "Mira Ashdown",
		"unit_b": "Branik",
		"title": "When Home Is a Smell",
		"text": "Branik is pulling bread from the firestone when Mira stops short, breath catching before she can hide it.\n\n\"Sorry,\" she says quickly. \"It just—\"\n\"Smells familiar,\" Branik finishes gently.\nShe nods, staring too hard at the loaf. \"I hate that something so ordinary can hurt this much.\"\nBranik sets the bread down between them and tears off the heel. \"That’s because ordinary things do most of the holding. Roof beams. Soup. Someone humming in the next room. When they’re gone, the world notices badly.\"\nMira takes the piece he offers, fingers trembling only a little. \"Do you ever stop missing it?\"\nBranik’s smile is warm and ruined around the edges. \"No. But sometimes you get good enough at feeding the living that missing home starts sounding less like an ending and more like a promise.\"",
