	{
		"id": "pair_inez_garrick_after_borders_fail",
		"unit_a": "Inez",
		"unit_b": "Garrick Vale",
		"title": "After Borders Fail",
		"text": "Inez is resetting snare bells along the perimeter when Garrick joins her with a map he no longer trusts.\n\n\"This line means nothing now,\" he says, staring at the ink.\nInez does not take the map. \"It meant something to someone. That is why it hurt people.\"\nHe folds it once, sharply. \"I was taught to honor borders.\"\n\"And I was taught to notice who bled when they moved,\" she replies.\nThat silences him.\nAfter a while, she points into the dark. \"There. Water. Windbreak. Good ground to keep people through the night.\"\nGarrick looks where she points, then folds the map smaller and puts it away. \"You always answer with land.\"\nInez’s voice is quiet. \"Land does not lie about what it can hold.\"",
