	{
		"id": "pair_tariq_sorrel_after_the_archive_opens",
		"unit_a": "Tariq",
		"unit_b": "Sorrel",
		"title": "After the Archive Opens",
		"text": "Sorrel is copying notes so quickly their ink keeps outrunning their hand. Tariq watches for a moment, then quietly moves the lamp closer.\n\n\"You are about to discover whether obsession can be diagnosed by penmanship,\" he says.\nSorrel startles, then blinks at the adjusted light. \"Thank you.\"\nHe waves that off. \"Do not make it sentimental. I only need you able to read your own catastrophe tomorrow.\"\nSorrel smiles despite their exhaustion. \"That was almost kind.\"\nTariq leans against the table, gaze softening in spite of himself. \"Knowledge this dangerous is easiest to survive when someone else in the room knows exactly why you are shaking.\"\nSorrel’s pen slows. \"You do.\"\n\"Unfortunately,\" Tariq says. \"Yes.\"",
