	{
		"id": "pair_celia_liora_after_verdict",
		"unit_a": "Celia",
		"unit_b": "Liora",
		"title": "After the Verdict",
		"text": "Celia stands in full harness though the camp has long since gone to rest. Liora approaches carrying two cups of tea and the sort of determination that has learned to look gentle on purpose.\n\n\"You are doing penance again,\" Liora says.\nCelia stiffens. \"I am standing watch.\"\n\"On no assigned post. In polished armor. Alone.\"\nThat almost makes Celia laugh. Almost.\nLiora offers her a cup. \"You do not have to become a monument every time the world reminds you what it once demanded of you.\"\nCelia takes the tea with both hands, as if it requires courage. \"And if standing still is the only thing keeping me from becoming that girl again?\"\nLiora’s answer comes steady and warm. \"Then let someone stand with you until it isn’t.\"",
