	{
		"id": "pair_yselle_maela_before_the_last_performance",
		"unit_a": "Yselle Maris",
		"unit_b": "Maela Thorn",
		"title": "Before the Last Performance",
		"text": "Yselle is pinning a ribbon into place with hands steadier than her breathing. Maela drops onto the crate beside her and immediately pretends not to notice.\n\n\"You do know this isn’t a stage,\" Maela says lightly.\n\"Everything with witnesses is a stage,\" Yselle replies.\nMaela turns that over, then bumps her shoulder gently against hers. \"And if tonight there are no witnesses?\"\nYselle’s smile turns fragile in a way she would hate being seen. \"Then perhaps I would not know where to put my hands.\"\nMaela takes one of them and holds it between both of hers without ceremony. \"Here,\" she says.\nFor once, Yselle does not answer with charm. She only squeezes back.",
