	{
		"id": "pair_nyx_maela_if_we_live",
		"unit_a": "Nyx",
		"unit_b": "Maela Thorn",
		"title": "If We Live",
		"text": "Maela is lying on her back atop the supply wagon, staring at the sky like it might offer useful gossip. Nyx appears below and tosses a pebble up at her.\n\n\"Elegant,\" Maela says.\n\"You were ignoring reality from a height again,\" Nyx replies.\nShe props herself up on one elbow. \"And you came all the way over here to object? That is almost tender.\"\nNyx folds their arms, expression guarded and exhausted all at once. \"If tomorrow goes badly, I would prefer not to discover I left things unsaid out of spite.\"\nThat wipes the grin from Maela’s face.\n\"Then say one,\" she says softly.\nNyx looks away first. \"If we live,\" they mutter, \"you are not allowed to vanish without warning.\"\nMaela’s answer is gentler than the night deserves. \"If we live, I’ll make you ask properly.\"",
