		{
		"id": "pair_darian_yselle_when_the_room_is_empty",
		"unit_a": "Darian",
		"unit_b": "Yselle Maris",
		"title": "When the Room Is Empty",
		"text": "The camp has gone quiet enough for the lanterns to sound loud. Yselle is removing the last of her stage paint when Darian pauses in the entrance, as if stepping any farther in would mean admitting something.\n\n\"You missed your cue,\" she says softly.\n\"I was waiting for the audience to leave,\" he replies.\nThat earns a small smile. \"And now?\"\nDarian studies her without wit for once. \"Now the room is honest. Dangerous change.\"\nYselle sets the cloth down. \"You only like rooms when they lie for you?\"\n\"No,\" he says, voice lower than usual. \"Only when I know what they will cost.\"\nShe steps closer, not enough to touch. \"And this one?\"\nHis smile is tired and real all at once. \"Ruination,\" he says. \"Probably.\" \nYselle’s answering look is warm enough to make the word sound survivable.",
