	{
		"id": "pair_nyx_maela_stay_visible",
		"unit_a": "Nyx",
		"unit_b": "Maela Thorn",
		"title": "Stay Visible",
		"text": "Maela is perched on the palisade again, impossible and bright against the dark. Nyx stops below her and does not bother pretending they were heading somewhere else.\n\n\"You do know there are easier ways to give me grey hairs,\" they mutter.\nMaela grins down at them. \"I didn’t know you were planning on keeping me long enough for that to matter.\"\nNyx opens their mouth, closes it, then looks away toward the tree line. \"That’s not fair.\"\nMaela drops lightly to the ground, all teasing gone now. \"No,\" she says. \"It isn’t.\"\nFor a moment they stand almost shoulder to shoulder.\n\"I’m bad at this part,\" Nyx admits.\n\"Which part?\"\nThey swallow. \"The part where I want someone to stay visible.\"\nMaela’s answer is quiet and immediate. \"Then keep looking at me.\"",
