	{
		"id": "pair_kaelen_liora_held_together",
		"unit_a": "Kaelen",
		"unit_b": "Liora",
		"title": "Held Together",
		"text": "Liora finds Kaelen re-binding an old leather grip that no longer strictly needs saving. She sits beside him without asking.\n\n\"You repair things when you cannot sleep,\" she says.\n\"I have been caught,\" he replies.\n\"Mm.\" She folds her hands in her lap. \"I pray when I cannot sleep. Which is really just repairing my thoughts with different tools.\"\nThat brings the faintest curve to his mouth.\n\"And does it work?\" he asks.\nLiora considers the question honestly. \"Sometimes. Usually it just keeps me from breaking in one clean direction.\"\nKaelen’s hands still on the leather. After a long silence, he says, \"There are worse ways to be held together.\"\nWhen she leans her shoulder lightly against his, he does not move away.",
