	{
		"id": "pair_celia_veska_resting_weight",
		"unit_a": "Celia",
		"unit_b": "Veska Moor",
		"title": "Resting Weight",
		"text": "Celia is trying to remove her armor one buckle at a time without acknowledging how tired she is. Veska appears, takes one of the straps in hand, and waits.\n\n\"I can manage,\" Celia says automatically.\n\"I know,\" Veska replies. \"That was not the question.\"\nSomething in Celia’s face shifts, small and painful.\nVeska loosens the strap with calm, practiced hands. \"You do not always have to be the shape the war asked for.\"\nCelia’s voice is barely above a whisper. \"I don’t know who I am when I set it down.\"\nVeska’s answer comes warm and certain. \"Then set down one piece at a time. I’ll stay until the answer starts to look like you.\" \nFor once, Celia lets someone else carry part of the weight.",
