	{
		"id": "pair_tamsin_liora_gentle_hands",
		"unit_a": "Tamsin Reed",
		"unit_b": "Liora",
		"title": "Gentle Hands",
		"text": "Tamsin is trying to thread a needle through trembling fingers when Liora reaches out and steadies her wrist.\n\n\"Sorry,\" Tamsin says immediately. \"I know. I should rest. I just—\"\n\"You do not have to apologize before I have even been kind to you,\" Liora says, and the softness of it nearly undoes her.\nTamsin laughs once, breathless and embarrassed. \"That sounds made up.\"\nLiora smiles, small and tired. \"Most mercy does, the first time you hear it plainly.\"\nThe needle finally slips through. Tamsin watches their hands for a moment longer than necessary.\n\"You make it look easy,\" she murmurs.\nLiora’s thumb brushes lightly over her knuckles before she lets go. \"No,\" she says. \"I just think it is worth doing carefully.\"",
