	{
		"id": "pair_tariq_sorrel_shared_lamplight",
		"unit_a": "Tariq",
		"unit_b": "Sorrel",
		"title": "Shared Lamplight",
		"text": "Sorrel has fallen asleep over a page of copied notes, cheek pillowed on their forearm. Tariq notices first, pretends he did not, then quietly moves the lamp so the heat won’t singe the paper.\n\nSorrel wakes just enough to notice him. \"You didn’t leave,\" they murmur.\nTariq keeps his eyes on the annotations. \"I considered it. Then I decided someone ought to be here in case your scholarship attempted self-immolation.\"\nEven half-asleep, Sorrel smiles. \"That was almost sweet.\"\n\"Do not spread that rumor.\" He pauses, then adds more quietly, \"You think more gently than the world deserves. Someone should keep an eye on the edges while you do it.\"\nSorrel blinks up at him through exhaustion and candlelight. \"You already are,\" they say.\nHe does not deny it.",
