	{
		"id": "pair_garrick_sabine_the_quiet_yes",
		"unit_a": "Garrick Vale",
		"unit_b": "Sabine Varr",
		"title": "The Quiet Yes",
		"text": "Sabine is still working when Garrick returns from the perimeter and sets a folded cloak over the back of her chair.\n\n\"You’ll chill,\" he says.\nShe glances at the cloak, then at him. \"That was almost tender of you.\"\nGarrick’s mouth twitches. \"Careful. I have a reputation for stern dignity to maintain.\"\nSabine finally leans back, letting the fabric settle around her shoulders. \"And if I said I found that reputation less persuasive than the man carrying it?\"\nFor perhaps the first time in recorded history, Garrick Vale has no immediate answer.\nHe steps closer instead, one gloved hand resting on the chair between them.\n\"Then,\" he says at last, voice low and terribly controlled, \"I would ask whether that was meant kindly.\"\nSabine’s expression softens into something rare. \"Yes,\" she says. \"Quietly. But yes.\"",
