	{
		"id": "pair_mira_maela_when_the_air_is_safe",
		"unit_a": "Mira Ashdown",
		"unit_b": "Maela Thorn",
		"title": "When the Air Is Safe",
		"text": "Maela coaxes Mira onto the highest intact watchpoint in camp with the solemn promise that no one else will bother them there.\n\n\"You keep doing this,\" Mira says, looking out over the dark. \"Taking me somewhere the ground can’t follow.\"\nMaela shrugs, trying for casual and missing by a mile. \"You breathe better up high.\"\nMira is quiet for a long time. Then: \"I think I breathe better when I know you’ll still be there when I look sideways.\"\nThat knocks all the easy grin out of Maela.\n\"I can do that,\" she says, suddenly, fiercely serious. \"I’m very good at inconvenient persistence.\"\nMira laughs, small and shaken and fond. When their shoulders touch, neither of them pretends it was accidental.",
