	{
		"id": "pair_yselle_maela_hold_still",
		"unit_a": "Yselle Maris",
		"unit_b": "Maela Thorn",
		"title": "Hold Still",
		"text": "Yselle is trying to pin a tear in her sleeve one-handed when Maela reaches over and catches the fabric before she can jab herself.\n\n\"You are impossible to assist gracefully,\" Yselle says.\n\"I contain multitudes,\" Maela replies, grinning. Then, softer: \"Hold still.\"\nYselle does. That may be the more surprising miracle.\nMaela’s fingers are deft in a completely different way than they are on rooftops or rigging. She smooths the seam flat with absent care.\n\"There,\" she says. \"No one will notice.\"\nYselle’s gaze lingers on her face, not the mended cloth. \"That was not really the part I was worried about.\"\nMaela looks up too fast, and suddenly the space between them feels deliberate.\n\"No?\"\nYselle smiles, warm and dangerous in equal measure. \"No.\"",
