	{
		"id": "pair_nyx_darian_if_i_stay",
		"unit_a": "Nyx",
		"unit_b": "Darian",
		"title": "If I Stay",
		"text": "Darian finds Nyx alone near the supply wagons, knife in hand, cutting old cord down to useful lengths.\n\n\"You always look busiest when you’re about to leave emotionally,\" he says.\nNyx doesn’t glance up. \"And you always sound unbearable when you’re right.\"\nHe crouches beside them anyway. For once, he doesn’t fill the silence with charm.\nAfter a while, Nyx says, \"I was never built for staying.\"\nDarian’s answer is unexpectedly gentle. \"Neither was I. That has stopped neither of us from becoming someone’s problem on purpose.\"\nThat wins a laugh out of them, unwilling and real.\nNyx looks at him then, something rawer than sarcasm in their face. \"And if I stay badly?\"\nDarian’s smile is tired, fond, and far too honest. \"Then I shall simply have to admire you persistently until it improves.\"",
